<br>
Personally, I found acquiring AA at level 60 <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">very</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> satisfying.  I have 86 AA, with 11 AA banked for 63, and so far have:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>General:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Run 3, Regen 3, Int 3, First Aid 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Archetype:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Mastery, Fury</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Subtlety</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, all at 3<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Class:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Pet Discipline, Elemental Pact, Improved Reclaim Energy, Quick Summoning 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>PoP:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Fury of Magic 1</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I don't regret a single one of these, and I found them all very useful.<br>
<br>
One way to think of it is in terms of hours, and compare AA to gear.  How many hours would you camp for a magic item that gave you an AA?  Even better, an item that occupied a completely new inventory slot so you did not have to swap out something nice that you are already wearing?<br>
<br>
It took me about 4 hours on average, mostly soloing with interruptions and playing guild officer, to get an AA.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Mastery 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> took 2+4+6=12 AA * 4 hours or less than 50 hours to reduce the cost of all my spells by 10%.  How many hours would you have to farm for an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Obulus Death Shroud</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or the platinum to buy it?  Oh and it stacks with all your equipment.  <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">And</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> you can farm AA nearly <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">anywhere</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> with your friends <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">anytime</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, rather than be tied to some specific camp which may or may not be free.  Indeed, I concluded that:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>AA &gt;&gt; Gear</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
At least for a casual player like myself.<br>
<br>
I can say that being 60 and farming AA has been the best part of my career so far.  I don't have enough hours in PoP to really evaluate it, but based on what I read, I think I will delay leveling past 63rd.<br>
<br>
